  "summaries": [
    "<b>Flaming Arrows</b> are a type of <linked>arrow</linked>. They are an upgrade to the <linked>Wooden Arrow</linked>, dealing slightly more damage and having a chance to inflict the <linked>On Fire!</linked> <linked>debuff</linked> on <linked>enemies</linked>. They are fairly easy to craft, requiring only <linked>Torches</linked> and <linked>Wooden Arrows</linked>.",
    "Flaming Arrows emit light when fired or dropped, making them useful for temporary lighting in a cave. However, they will not emit light if fired into <linked>water</linked>. <span class=\"eico i3 i5 i6\" title=\"Old-gen console, 3DS and Legacy tModLoader versions\"><b></b><i></i></span> Flaming Arrows are recoverable after hitting a wall or enemy 1/3 of the time, but only 1/3 of those that do remain lit; the rest drop as Wooden Arrows. Wooden Arrows fired from the <linked>Molten Fury</linked> behave similarly and have a chance to be recovered as Flaming Arrows."
